      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The notion that specific ancestral or ethnic lineages possess predetermined physiological advantages like higher fast-twitch fiber percentages is largely speculative and unsupported by robust, peer-reviewed sports science. Any observed differences are usually the result of environmental factors, diet, and training history, not immutable biological traits tied to ancestry. Therefore, basing training adjustments on generalized ethnic characteristics is scientifically unsound and unprofessional. You should treat each client as a unique individual, regardless of their background.",
