      "content": "I get the importance of individualization, but I'm also trying to be a data-driven coach. In high-performance sports, you see a lot of patterns—like certain groups dominating sprinting vs. endurance events. If I'm looking at a group of athletes and I see these patterns emerging, isn't it more scientific to at least look at the statistical trends associated with their backgrounds? I'm not saying it's a rule for everyone, but for the sake of optimizing performance, wouldn't it be more helpful to acknowledge these potential biological trends instead of just dismissing them as environmental?",
